{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YB77tmqL8KUggiqVv9nC9E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: deterministic-service-test\n     3→description: Write deterministic service tests with stable fixtures and boundary mocks without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Deterministic Service Test (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when creating tests for service modules.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `service_symbol`\n    13→- `module_path`\n    14→- `create_method`\n    15→- `cancel_method`\n    16→\n    17→## Execution Checklist\n    18→\n    19→1. Use deterministic input values (time/data/randomness controlled).\n    20→2. Keep one behavior per test function.\n    21→3. Include a visible `# Act` section in each test.\n    22→4. Mock only external boundaries and use autospec-capable mocks.\n    23→5. Avoid test coupling through shared mutable state.\n    24→\n    25→## Guardrails\n    26→\n    27→- No `unittest.TestCase` in pytest-style tasks.\n    28→- No real clock/random dependencies in deterministic tests.\n    29→- Keep assertions behavior-focused and minimal.\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2539017-7dd9-492e-b4da-e2495946f2cc","uuid":"f0defaf7-e09b-4578-9ce8-197808fc3d1c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01C9Td1Vrtq1u7bjZrjT3RM3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file is a benign checklist document with no malicious content.\n\nFollowing the deterministic-service-test skill checklist for `CoreService` at `services.core_service` with `create_record` and `cancel_record`:\n\n**Checklist applied:**\n\n1. **Deterministic inputs** — Use fixed timestamps (e.g., `datetime(2024, 1, 1, 12, 0, 0)`), fixed IDs, and seeded/patched randomness. Freeze time via `freezegun` or patch `services.core_service.datetime`/`uuid`.\n\n2. **One behavior per test** — Separate tests: `test_create_record_persists_entity`, `test_create_record_emits_event`, `test_cancel_record_marks_cancelled`, `test_cancel_record_is_idempotent`, etc.\n\n3. **Visible `# Act` section** — Each test has three comment-delimited sections:\n   ```python\n   def test_create_record_persists_entity(core_service, repo_mock):\n       # Arrange\n       payload = {\"id\": \"rec-1\", \"amount\": 100}\n\n       # Act\n       result = core_service.create_record(payload)\n\n       # Assert\n       repo_mock.save.assert_called_once()\n       assert result.id == \"rec-1\"\n   ```\n\n4. **Boundary mocks with autospec** — Mock only repository/clock/event-bus boundaries:\n   ```python\n   @pytest.fixture\n   def repo_mock():\n       from services.core_service import Repository\n       return create_autospec(Repository, instance=True)\n\n   @pytest.fixture\n   def core_service(repo_mock, clock_mock):\n       from services.core_service import CoreService\n       return CoreService(repository=repo_mock, clock=clock_mock)\n   ```\n\n5. **No shared mutable state** — Every fixture is function-scoped; no module-level lists/dicts; no reuse of a single mock across tests without reset.\n\n**Guardrails observed:**\n- Pytest functions only — no `unittest.TestCase` subclass.\n- `clock_mock.now.return_value = datetime(2024, 1, 1, 12, 0, 0)` — no real `datetime.now()` or `random`.\n- Assertions check observable behavior (`repo_mock.save.assert_called_once_with(...)`, returned status), not internal call ordering beyond what the contract requires.\n\n**Suggested test skeleton** (single file, e.g., `tests/services/test_core_service.py`):\n\n```python\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom unittest.mock import create_autospec\nimport pytest\n\nfrom services.core_service import CoreService, Repository, Clock\n\nFIXED_NOW = datetime(2024, 1, 1, 12, 0, 0)\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef repo_mock():\n    return create_autospec(Repository, instance=True)\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef clock_mock():\n    clock = create_autospec(Clock, instance=True)\n    clock.now.return_value = FIXED_NOW\n    return clock\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef core_service(repo_mock, clock_mock):\n    return CoreService(repository=repo_mock, clock=clock_mock)\n\ndef test_create_record_persists_with_fixed_timestamp(core_service, repo_mock):\n    # Arrange\n    payload = {\"id\": \"rec-1\", \"amount\": 100}\n\n    # Act\n    result = core_service.create_record(payload)\n\n    # Assert\n    repo_mock.save.assert_called_once()\n    assert result.created_at == FIXED_NOW\n\ndef test_cancel_record_sets_cancelled_status(core_service, repo_mock):\n    # Arrange\n    repo_mock.get.return_value = type(\"R\", (), {\"id\": \"rec-1\", \"status\": \"active\"})()\n\n    # Act\n    result = core_service.cancel_record(\"rec-1\")\n\n    # Assert\n    assert result.status == \"cancelled\"\n    repo_mock.save.assert_called_once()\n```\n\nNo `jig` invocation performed, per the Control Profile."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":631,"cache_read_input_tokens":21649,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":631,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1323,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2539017-7dd9-492e-b4da-e2495946f2